# iOS Xcode Project Rules

## CRITICAL: project.pbxproj must stay in sync

When creating or referencing any new `.swift` file under `client/ios/App/App/`:
- The file MUST be added to `project.pbxproj` in ALL of these places:
  1. `PBXBuildFile` section (compile reference)
  2. `PBXFileReference` section (file on disk reference)
  3. The `App` PBXGroup's `children` list
  4. `PBXSourcesBuildPhase` `files` list
- If ANY of these are missing, the Swift file will exist on disk but never be compiled. If the storyboard references a class from that file, the app will show a blank screen.

## Never change Main.storyboard customClass without verifying project.pbxproj

- NEVER change `Main.storyboard` to reference a `customClass` unless that class's `.swift` file is already listed in the `PBXSourcesBuildPhase` of `project.pbxproj`.
- The safe default is `customClass="CAPBridgeViewController"` with `customModule="Capacitor"`. Only change this if the replacement class is confirmed to be in the compile sources.

## After any iOS native changes

- Always tell the user to open Xcode and verify the file appears in Build Phases > Compile Sources before building.
